</div>
<div class="row">
	<p class="mr-auto ml-auto" style="font-family: 'Lato'; font-style:italic"><%= "it's clickable" %> </p>
	<br>
</div>
<div class=" row z">
	<p class="typical"><%= "We then proceeded to make the prototype and conduct a few contextual inquiries with sorority and fraternity members. From those, we found out that the colors used in the app are important to some members as the colors they use in their greek organizations hold meaning and as such advised us to change it. Moreover, they expressed that they liked the idea of being able to create their own feeds and their own forums to be able to communicate with each other as it removes the need for multiple channels and Facebook pages for information. Lastly, they also commented that they liked the idea of being able to see what public events are happening around the university through the Events and AroundMe function."  %>
	</p>
	<br>
</div>
